Using Python3.5.2 :: Anaconda 4.2.0 (x86_64)

Requires Keras
    1. download source using >>> git clone https://github.com/fchollet/keras.git
    2. >>> cd keras
    3. install using >>> python setup.py install

Configure Keras to use "theano" instead of "tensorflow"
    1. >>> vi ~/.keras/keras.json
    2. edit backend from "tensorflow" to "theano"

Install graphing packaes
    1. >>> conda install graphviz
    2. >>> pip install git+https://github.com/nlhepler/pydot.git
    Alternatively
    2.a >>> git clone https://github.com/nlhepler/pydot.git
    2.b >>> cd pydot
    2.c >>> python setup.py install
